51struct GraphBuilder {
52 Zone* phase_zone;
53 Schedule& schedule;
54 Linkage* linkage;
55
56 Isolate* isolate;
57 JSHeapBroker* broker;
58 Zone* graph_zone;
59 using AssemblerT = TSAssembler<ExplicitTruncationReducer>;
60 AssemblerT assembler;
61 SourcePositionTable* source_positions;
62 NodeOriginTable* origins;
63 TurboshaftPipelineKind pipeline_kind;

65 GraphBuilder(PipelineData* data, Zone* phase_zone, Schedule& schedule,
66 Linkage* linkage)
67 : phase_zone(phase_zone),
68 schedule(schedule),
69 linkage(linkage),
70 isolate(data->isolate()),
71 broker(data->broker()),
72 graph_zone(data->graph_zone()),
73 assembler(data, data->graph(), data->graph(), phase_zone),
74 source_positions(data->source_positions()),
75 origins(data->node_origins()),
76 pipeline_kind(data->pipeline_kind()) {}

79 Block* block;
80 OpIndex final_frame_state;

84 bool inside_region = false;

90 template <typename T>
91 V<T> Map(Node* old_node) {
92 V<T> result = V<T>::Cast(op_mapping.Get(old_node));
93 DCHECK(__ output_graph().IsValid(result));
94 return result;
95 }

97 OpIndex Map(Node* old_node) {
98 OpIndex result = op_mapping.Get(old_node);
99 DCHECK(__ output_graph().IsValid(result));
100 return result;
101 }

103 Block* Map(BasicBlock* block) {
104 Block* result = block_mapping[block->rpo_number()].block;
105 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(result);
106 return result;
107 }

109 void FixLoopPhis(BasicBlock* loop) {
110 DCHECK(loop->IsLoopHeader());
111 for (Node* node : *loop->nodes()) {
112 if (node->opcode() != IrOpcode::kPhi) {
113 continue;
114 }
115 OpIndex phi_index = Map(node);
116 PendingLoopPhiOp& pending_phi =
117 __ output_graph().Get(phi_index).Cast<PendingLoopPhiOp>();
118 __ output_graph().Replace<PhiOp>(
119 phi_index,
120 base::VectorOf({pending_phi.first(), Map(node->InputAt(1))}),
121 pending_phi.rep);
122 }
123 }

125 void ProcessDeoptInput(FrameStateData::Builder* builder, Node* input,
126 MachineType type) {
127 DCHECK_NE(input->opcode(), IrOpcode::kObjectState);
128 DCHECK_NE(input->opcode(), IrOpcode::kStateValues);
129 DCHECK_NE(input->opcode(), IrOpcode::kTypedStateValues);
130 if (input->opcode() == IrOpcode::kObjectId) {
131 builder->AddDematerializedObjectReference(ObjectIdOf(input->op()));
132 } else if (input->opcode() == IrOpcode::kTypedObjectState) {
133 const TypedObjectStateInfo& info =
134 OpParameter<TypedObjectStateInfo>(input->op());
135 int field_count = input->op()->ValueInputCount();
136 builder->AddDematerializedObject(info.object_id(),
137 static_cast<uint32_t>(field_count));
138 for (int i = 0; i < field_count; ++i) {
139 ProcessDeoptInput(builder, input->InputAt(i),
140 (*info.machine_types())[i]);
141 }
142 } else if (input->opcode() == IrOpcode::kArgumentsElementsState) {
143 builder->AddArgumentsElements(ArgumentsStateTypeOf(input->op()));
144 } else if (input->opcode() == IrOpcode::kArgumentsLengthState) {
145 builder->AddArgumentsLength();
146 } else {
147 builder->AddInput(type, Map(input));
148 }
149 }
150
151 void ProcessStateValues(FrameStateData::Builder* builder,
152 Node* state_values) {
153 for (auto it = StateValuesAccess(state_values).begin(); !it.done(); ++it) {
154 if (Node* node = it.node()) {
155 ProcessDeoptInput(builder, node, (*it).type);
156 } else {
157 builder->AddUnusedRegister();
158 }
159 }
160 }
161
162 void BuildFrameStateData(FrameStateData::Builder* builder,
163 compiler::FrameState frame_state) {
164 if (frame_state.outer_frame_state()->opcode() != IrOpcode::kStart) {
165 builder->AddParentFrameState(Map(frame_state.outer_frame_state()));
166 }
167 ProcessDeoptInput(builder, frame_state.function(),
168 MachineType::AnyTagged());
169 ProcessStateValues(builder, frame_state.parameters());
170 ProcessDeoptInput(builder, frame_state.context(), MachineType::AnyTagged());
171 ProcessStateValues(builder, frame_state.locals());
172 Node* stack = frame_state.stack();
173 if (v8_flags.turboshaft_frontend) {
174 // If we run graph building before Turbofan's SimplifiedLowering, the
175 // `stack` input of frame states is still a single deopt input, rather
176 // than a StateValues node.
177 if (stack->opcode() == IrOpcode::kHeapConstant &&
178 *HeapConstantOf(stack->op()) ==
179 ReadOnlyRoots(isolate->heap()).optimized_out()) {
180 // Nothing to do in this case.
181 } else {
182 const Operation& accumulator_op = __ output_graph().Get(Map(stack));
183 const RegisterRepresentation accumulator_rep =
184 accumulator_op.outputs_rep()[0];
185 MachineType type;
186 switch (accumulator_rep.value()) {
187 case RegisterRepresentation::Tagged():
188 type = MachineType::AnyTagged();
189 break;
190 default:
191 UNIMPLEMENTED();
192 }
193 ProcessDeoptInput(builder, stack, type);
194 }
195 } else {
196 ProcessStateValues(builder, stack);
197 }
198 }

200 Block::Kind BlockKind(BasicBlock* block) {
201 switch (block->front()->opcode()) {
202 case IrOpcode::kStart:
203 case IrOpcode::kEnd:
204 case IrOpcode::kMerge:
205 return Block::Kind::kMerge;
206 case IrOpcode::kIfTrue:
207 case IrOpcode::kIfFalse:
208 case IrOpcode::kIfValue:
209 case IrOpcode::kIfDefault:
210 case IrOpcode::kIfSuccess:
211 case IrOpcode::kIfException:
212 return Block::Kind::kBranchTarget;
213 case IrOpcode::kLoop:
214 return Block::Kind::kLoopHeader;
215 default:
216 block->front()->Print();
217 UNIMPLEMENTED();
218 }
219 }
220 OpIndex Process(Node* node, BasicBlock* block,
221 const base::SmallVector<int, 16>& predecessor_permutation,
222 OpIndex& dominating_frame_state,
223 base::Optional<BailoutReason>* bailout,
224 bool is_final_control = false);
225};

227base::Optional<BailoutReason> GraphBuilder::Run() {
228 for (BasicBlock* block : *schedule.rpo_order()) {
229 block_mapping[block->rpo_number()].block =
230 block->IsLoopHeader() ? __ NewLoopHeader() : __ NewBlock();
231 }
232
233 for (BasicBlock* block : *schedule.rpo_order()) {
234 Block* target_block = Map(block);
235 if (!__ Bind(target_block)) continue;
236
237 // Since we visit blocks in rpo-order, the new block predecessors are sorted
238 // in rpo order too. However, the input schedule does not order
239 // predecessors, so we have to apply a corresponding permutation to phi
240 // inputs.
241 const BasicBlockVector& predecessors = block->predecessors();
242 base::SmallVector<int, 16> predecessor_permutation(predecessors.size());
243 std::iota(predecessor_permutation.begin(), predecessor_permutation.end(),
244 0);
245 std::sort(predecessor_permutation.begin(), predecessor_permutation.end(),
246 [&](size_t i, size_t j) {
247 return predecessors[i]->rpo_number() <
248 predecessors[j]->rpo_number();
249 });
250
251 OpIndex dominating_frame_state = OpIndex::Invalid();
252 if (!predecessors.empty()) {
253 dominating_frame_state =
254 block_mapping[predecessors[0]->rpo_number()].final_frame_state;
255 for (size_t i = 1; i < predecessors.size(); ++i) {
256 if (block_mapping[predecessors[i]->rpo_number()].final_frame_state !=
257 dominating_frame_state) {
258 dominating_frame_state = OpIndex::Invalid();
259 break;
260 }
261 }
262 }
263 base::Optional<BailoutReason> bailout = base::nullopt;
264 for (Node* node : *block->nodes()) {
265 if (V8_UNLIKELY(node->InputCount() >=
266 int{std::numeric_limits<
267 decltype(Operation::input_count)>::max()})) {
268 return BailoutReason::kTooManyArguments;
269 }
270 OpIndex i = Process(node, block, predecessor_permutation,
271 dominating_frame_state, &bailout);
272 if (V8_UNLIKELY(bailout)) return bailout;
273 if (!__ current_block()) break;
274 op_mapping.Set(node, i);
275 }
276 // We have terminated this block with `Unreachable`, so we stop generation
277 // here and continue with the next block.
278 if (!__ current_block()) continue;
279
280 if (Node* node = block->control_input()) {
281 if (V8_UNLIKELY(node->InputCount() >=
282 int{std::numeric_limits<
283 decltype(Operation::input_count)>::max()})) {
284 return BailoutReason::kTooManyArguments;
285 }
286 OpIndex i = Process(node, block, predecessor_permutation,
287 dominating_frame_state, &bailout, true);
288 if (V8_UNLIKELY(bailout)) return bailout;
289 op_mapping.Set(node, i);
290 }
291 switch (block->control()) {
292 case BasicBlock::kGoto: {
293 DCHECK_EQ(block->SuccessorCount(), 1);
294 Block* destination = Map(block->SuccessorAt(0));
295 __ Goto(destination);
296 if (destination->IsBound()) {
297 DCHECK(destination->IsLoop());
298 FixLoopPhis(block->SuccessorAt(0));
299 }
300 break;
301 }
302 case BasicBlock::kBranch:
303 case BasicBlock::kSwitch:
304 case BasicBlock::kReturn:
305 case BasicBlock::kDeoptimize:
306 case BasicBlock::kThrow:
307 case BasicBlock::kCall:
308 case BasicBlock::kTailCall:
309 break;
310 case BasicBlock::kNone:
311 UNREACHABLE();
312 }
313 DCHECK_NULL(__ current_block());
314
315 block_mapping[block->rpo_number()].final_frame_state =
316 dominating_frame_state;
317 }
318
319 if (source_positions->IsEnabled()) {
320 for (OpIndex index : __ output_graph().AllOperationIndices()) {
321 compiler::NodeId origin =
322 __ output_graph().operation_origins()[index].DecodeTurbofanNodeId();
323 __ output_graph().source_positions()[index] =
324 source_positions->GetSourcePosition(origin);
325 }
326 }
327
328 if (origins) {
329 for (OpIndex index : __ output_graph().AllOperationIndices()) {
330 OpIndex origin = __ output_graph().operation_origins()[index];
331 origins->SetNodeOrigin(index.id(), origin.DecodeTurbofanNodeId());
332 }
333 }
334
335 return base::nullopt;
336}

338OpIndex GraphBuilder::Process(
339 Node* node, BasicBlock* block,
340 const base::SmallVector<int, 16>& predecessor_permutation,
341 OpIndex& dominating_frame_state, base::Optional<BailoutReason>* bailout,
342 bool is_final_control) {
343 if (Asm().current_block() == nullptr) {
344 return OpIndex::Invalid();
345 }
346 __ SetCurrentOrigin(OpIndex::EncodeTurbofanNodeId(node->id()));
347 const Operator* op = node->op();
348 Operator::Opcode opcode = op->opcode();
349 switch (opcode) {
350 case IrOpcode::kStart:
351 case IrOpcode::kMerge:
352 case IrOpcode::kLoop:
353 case IrOpcode::kIfTrue:
354 case IrOpcode::kIfFalse:
355 case IrOpcode::kIfDefault:
356 case IrOpcode::kIfValue:
357 case IrOpcode::kStateValues:
358 case IrOpcode::kTypedStateValues:
359 case IrOpcode::kObjectId:
360 case IrOpcode::kTypedObjectState:
361 case IrOpcode::kArgumentsElementsState:
362 case IrOpcode::kArgumentsLengthState:
363 case IrOpcode::kEffectPhi:
364 case IrOpcode::kTerminate:
365 return OpIndex::Invalid();
366
367 case IrOpcode::kCheckpoint: {
368 // Preserve the frame state from this checkpoint for following nodes.
369 dominating_frame_state = Map(NodeProperties::GetFrameStateInput(node));
370 return OpIndex::Invalid();
371 }
372
373 case IrOpcode::kIfException: {
374 return __ CatchBlockBegin();
375 }
376
377 case IrOpcode::kIfSuccess: {
378 return OpIndex::Invalid();
379 }
380
381 case IrOpcode::kParameter: {
382 const ParameterInfo& info = ParameterInfoOf(op);
383 RegisterRepresentation rep =
384 RegisterRepresentation::FromMachineRepresentation(
385 linkage->GetParameterType(ParameterIndexOf(node->op()))
386 .representation());
387 return __ Parameter(info.index(), rep, info.debug_name());
388 }
389
390 case IrOpcode::kOsrValue: {
391 return __ OsrValue(OsrValueIndexOf(op));
392 }
393
394 case IrOpcode::kPhi: {
395 int input_count = op->ValueInputCount();
396 RegisterRepresentation rep =
397 RegisterRepresentation::FromMachineRepresentation(
398 PhiRepresentationOf(op));
399 if (__ current_block()->IsLoop()) {
400 DCHECK_EQ(input_count, 2);
401 return __ PendingLoopPhi(Map(node->InputAt(0)), rep);
402 } else {
403 base::SmallVector<OpIndex, 16> inputs;
404 for (int i = 0; i < input_count; ++i) {
405 // If this predecessor end with an unreachable (and doesn't jump to
406 // this merge block), we skip its Phi input.
407 Block* pred = Map(block->PredecessorAt(predecessor_permutation[i]));
408 if (!pred->IsBound() ||
409 pred->LastOperation(__ output_graph()).Is<UnreachableOp>()) {
410 continue;
411 }
412 inputs.push_back(Map(node->InputAt(predecessor_permutation[i])));
413 }
414 return __ Phi(base::VectorOf(inputs), rep);
415 }
416 }
417
418 case IrOpcode::kInt64Constant:
419 return __ Word64Constant(static_cast<uint64_t>(OpParameter<int64_t>(op)));
420 case IrOpcode::kInt32Constant:
421 return __ Word32Constant(static_cast<uint32_t>(OpParameter<int32_t>(op)));
422 case IrOpcode::kFloat64Constant:
423 return __ Float64Constant(OpParameter<double>(op));
424 case IrOpcode::kFloat32Constant:
425 return __ Float32Constant(OpParameter<float>(op));
426 case IrOpcode::kNumberConstant:
427 return __ NumberConstant(OpParameter<double>(op));
428 case IrOpcode::kTaggedIndexConstant:
429 return __ TaggedIndexConstant(OpParameter<int32_t>(op));
430 case IrOpcode::kHeapConstant:
431 return __ HeapConstant(HeapConstantOf(op));
432 case IrOpcode::kCompressedHeapConstant:
433 return __ CompressedHeapConstant(HeapConstantOf(op));
434 case IrOpcode::kExternalConstant:
435 return __ ExternalConstant(OpParameter<ExternalReference>(op));
436 case IrOpcode::kRelocatableInt64Constant:
437 return __ RelocatableConstant(
438 OpParameter<RelocatablePtrConstantInfo>(op).value(),
439 OpParameter<RelocatablePtrConstantInfo>(op).rmode());

523 OpIndex left = Map(node->InputAt(0));
524 OpIndex right = Map(node->InputAt(1));
525 if constexpr (kTaggedSize == kInt32Size) {
526 // Unfortunately, CSA produces Word32Equal for tagged comparison.
527 if (V8_UNLIKELY(pipeline_kind == TurboshaftPipelineKind::kCSA)) {
528 // We need to detect these cases and construct a consistent graph.
529 const bool left_is_tagged =
530 __ output_graph().Get(left).outputs_rep().at(0) ==
531 RegisterRepresentation::Tagged();
532 const bool right_is_tagged =
533 __ output_graph().Get(right).outputs_rep().at(0) ==
534 RegisterRepresentation::Tagged();

536 return __ TaggedEqual(V<Object>::Cast(left),

541 __ BitcastTaggedToWordPtr(V<Object>::Cast(left))),
542 V<Word32>::Cast(right));
543 } else if (right_is_tagged) {
544 return __ Word32Equal(
545 V<Word32>::Cast(left),
546 __ TruncateWordPtrToWord32(
547 __ BitcastTaggedToWordPtr(V<Object>::Cast(right))));

2021 base::VectorOf(slow_call_arguments),
2022 TSCallDescriptor::Create(params.descriptor(),
